# Backend API Rules

## Auth on Every Route
Every route handler must start with:
  const supabase = createClient()
  const { data: { user }, error } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
  if (!user) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 })

## Response Shape
Always return consistent shape:
  Success: { success: true, data: T }
  Error:   { success: false, error: string }
  
Use NextResponse.json() — never Response.json()

## Input Validation
Every POST route:
  const body = await request.json()
  const parsed = SomeSchema.safeParse(body)
  if (!parsed.success) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: parsed.error.message }, { status: 400 })

## Route Responsibilities

### POST /api/documents
- Validate file type (PDF, md, txt only) and size (max 10MB)
- Upload to Supabase Storage: path = `{userId}/{fileId}/{filename}`
- Trigger Trigger.dev job: ingest-document
- Return: { fileId, status: 'processing' }

### POST /api/jobs
- Accept: { jobUrl?: string, rawText?: string }
- If URL: call browser/extract.ts to scrape job posting
- Validate extracted text > 200 chars
- Trigger: orchestrator.runJobAnalysis()
- Return: { jobId, analysis: JobAnalysis }

### POST /api/generate  (streaming)
- Accept: { jobId, userId }
- Return: ReadableStream (SSE)
- Use Vercel AI SDK's createStreamableValue or manual SSE
- Run orchestrator.runFullPipeline() — pipe stream events to response
- On complete: save generated content to Supabase

### POST /api/apply
- Accept: { applicationId } (user has confirmed the generated content)
- Trigger: Trigger.dev job: submit-application
- Return: { jobId, status: 'submitting' }

## Rate Limiting
/api/generate: 10 calls per user per day (Upstash Redis rate limiter)
/api/apply: 10 calls per user per day
Return 429 with message: "Daily limit reached. Resets at midnight UTC."

## Trigger.dev Webhook
POST /api/webhooks/trigger
- Verify webhook signature
- Update job status in Supabase based on event type
- Emit real-time update via Supabase Realtime to frontend
